article.headline: Delaware 81, Bucknell 68
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Jawan Carter scored 26 points and Delaware scored the last 25 points of the game, rallying from 12 points down for an 81-68 victory over Bucknell on Saturday. Marc Egerson had 18 points and 13 rebounds, Alphonso Dawson added 15 points and 11 rebounds, and Brian Johnson scored 13 points for Delaware (12-17), which erased a 68-56, 12-point deficit in a four-minute span. Egerson dropped in a layup to tie the score at 68-all with just over three minutes left and the Blue Hens closed out the win with 13 more unanswered points. Patrick Behan scored 23 points, G.W. Boon added 16, and Bryan Cohen and Justin Castleberry each had 11 for Bucknell (6-21), which shot 37 percent (10-for-27) in the second half.
